<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER - REMOVE
        AND INSTALL - EGC WARNING LAMPS AND GAUGE WARNING LAMPS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>EGC WARNING LAMPS AND GAUGE WARNING LAMPS</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s08290_124.xml" xrefid="f08290554">EGC Exploded View</hotlnk>.
            <xref refid="f08290554"/>
        </para>
        <para>The EGC warning lamps and warning lamps are integral parts of the EGC circuit board. To replace the lamps
            the failed lamp must be cut out of the circuit board and a twist in lamp must be used to replace it.
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Remove the EGC from the instrument panel.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Remove six screws holding the back of the EGC in place and remove the back cover.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Locate the failed lamp and cut it out of the circuit board.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Replace the removed lamp with a twist in indicator lamp.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
    </svcproc>
